We have:
\begin{align*}
2^{-1} + 2^{-2} + 2^{-3} + 2^{-4} + 2^{-5} + 2^{-6} &= \frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{16} + \frac{1}{32} + \frac{1}{64} \\
&= \frac{32 + 16 + 8 + 4 + 2 + 1}{64} \\
&= \frac{63}{64}.
\end{align*}

Now we will find $63 \pmod{13}$:
\begin{align*}
63 &\equiv 8 \pmod{13}.
\end{align*}

Therefore, $2^{-1} + 2^{-2} + 2^{-3} + 2^{-4} + 2^{-5} + 2^{-6} \equiv \frac{63}{64} \equiv \frac{8}{64} \equiv \frac{8}{-1} \equiv -8 \equiv 5 \pmod{13}$.

Hence, the answer is $\boxed{5}$.

